text: Nataša Pirc Musar (born May 9, 1968) is a Slovenian attorney and author. She is the 5th President of Slovenia since December 23, 2022. She is the former Information Commissioner and former president of the Slovenian Red Cross (2015–2016). She is the first female president of Slovenia. ==References== Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:People from Ljubljana Category:Slovenian writers Category:Slovenian lawyers Category:Presidents of Slovenia Category:Current national leaders
